[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, LOG, AND POST-MARKET SURVEILLANCE ──────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User utterances                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generated assistant responses                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active care-pathway-corpus version                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active social-determinant-resource-directory version │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Final disposition                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Care-coordination-specific retention discipline]       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Retention sized to longest of HIPAA's six-year       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      minimum, state-specific medical-record retention     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      rules, FDA SaMD post-market obligations where        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      applicable, and any litigation-hold obligations      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Sensitive-disclosure surface separately governed     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      with restricted access                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Outcome correlation as long-time-horizon commitment]   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Multi-quarter to multi-year implementation           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Owned jointly by care-management leadership,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      operations, and data science                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort tracking                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement rate by patient cohort                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Attrition rate by patient cohort                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Appointment-completion rate                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Referral-closure rate                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Time-to-first-specialist-visit                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Post-discharge readmission rate                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Medication-reconciliation-accuracy rate              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Social-determinant-resource-utilization rate         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Warm-handoff completion rate                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Companion-pattern-violation rate                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Citation-coverage rate                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices (language, channel,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      condition, age cohort, sex, social-determinant       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      flags)                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled clinical-and-operational quality review]       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of escalations,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      handoffs, and low-confidence interactions            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers (care managers, operations, clinical       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      leadership) tag failure modes (out-of-scope,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      companion-pattern, missed-escalation, false-         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      escalation, integration-error, citation-gap, scope-  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      violation)                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-pathway-corpus revisions driven by review       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      findings with care-management-and-clinical-          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      leadership sign-off                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    care-pathway-corpus-revision proposals]                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-system integration as architectural primitive.** The assistant's value depends on integration depth. Each integration (EHR, referral management, scheduling, pharmacy, ADT feed, connected devices, social-determinant-resource directory, care-management platform, HIE) is a multi-quarter engineering and governance commitment with versioned data contracts, idempotency discipline, error handling, and freshness monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-pathway-corpus governance with care-management-and-clinical-leadership ownership.** The care-pathway library is owned by care-management and clinical leadership, reviewed before adoption, reviewed annually, and re-reviewed when material updates are made.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-transition protocol discipline.** Transitions of care have specific protocols per transition type, with documented steps, escalation triggers, and outcome tracking. The post-discharge transition is the highest-leverage operational responsibility.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Operational-service-level-aware coordination.** The assistant knows the institution's service-level expectations and surfaces opportunities to act when expectations are at risk.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Consent-aware multi-source information sharing.** Consent enforcement is in the data layer. The assistant cannot compose responses from data it should not have seen.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Companion-pattern avoidance as architectural discipline.** The assistant does not simulate friendship, affection, or personhood. The system prompt, the output safety, the persona-and-tone evaluator, and the conversation review process all enforce this.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Warm-handoff infrastructure with capacity sizing.** The assistant is deployed with backstop nurse-care-manager capacity. The handoff is warm, with conversation context attached.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every care-pathway delivery, every patient-education answer, every care-team-directory reference is grounded in a cited source with version preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When uncertain, when the patient's responses are ambiguous, when the conversation drifts toward clinical judgment, the response defaults to "let me connect you with a person."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement, attrition, and outcome metrics vary by language, channel, condition, age cohort, sex, social-determinant flags, and care-journey complexity. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by care-management leadership, clinical leadership, operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When upstream systems are unreachable, the assistant degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble accessing your care information right now; if this is urgent please call your care team or 911 for emergencies." The graceful degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
